Compilation flags:
========================================
Enable : MODEL=HYDRO, GRAVITY, GREP, NLEVEL=4
Disable:

Default setup:
========================================
1. Enable external potential
   --> OPT__EXT_POT = 1
2. Maximum refinement level (MAX_LEVEL) = 3 or update the Input_Flag_Rho

Note:
========================================
1. A test problem for neutron star migration test
   --> initial condition `tovstar_short` is generated by solving TOV equation

2. The GREP is treated as external potential. To eanble GREP correction, one needs
   --> enable both GRAVITY and GREP compilation flags
   --> in the test problem initializer, assign

      Init_ExtPot_Ptr                = Init_ExtPot_GREP;
      Poi_UserWorkBeforePoisson_Ptr  = Poi_UserWorkBeforePoisson_GREP;

3. If `GREP_DEBUG` compilation flag is enabled, additional information will be output
   to standard output for debugging the constructed GREP
   --> see src/SelfGravity/CPU_Poisson/CPU_ComputeGREP.cpp for detail

4. The central density is recorded in Record__CentralDens
